  43. ‌let copy_chars_unix nchars =
  44.   let n = ref nchars in
  45.   while !n > 0 do
  46.     let m = input !inchan copy_buffer 0 (Int.min !n 256) in
  47.     if m = 0 then raise End_of_file;
  48.     output !outchan copy_buffer 0 m;
  49.     n := !n - m
  50.   done

  52. ‌let copy_chars_win32 nchars =
  53.   for _i = 1 to nchars do
  54.     let c = input_char !inchan in
  55.     if c <> '\r' then output_char !outchan c
  56.   done

  58. ‌let copy_chars =

  63. ‌let copy next =
  64.   assert (next >= !cur_point);
  65.   seek_in !inchan !cur_point;
  66.   copy_chars (next - !cur_point);
  67.   cur_point := next

  104. let insert_profile rw_exp ex =
  105.   let st = ex.pexp_loc.loc_start.Lexing.pos_cnum
  106.   and en = ex.pexp_loc.loc_end.Lexing.pos_cnum
  107.   and gh = ex.pexp_loc.loc_ghost
  108.   in
  109.   if gh || st = en then
  110.     rw_exp true ex
  111.   else begin
  112.     insert_action st en;
  113.     rw_exp false ex;
  114.   end


  117. let pos_len = ref 0

  119. ‌let init_rewrite modes mod_name =
  120.   cur_point := 0;
  121.   if !instr_mode then begin
  122.     fprintf !outchan "module %sProfiling = Profiling;; " modprefix;
  123.     fprintf !outchan "let %s%s_cnt = Array.make 000000000" idprefix mod_name;
  124.     pos_len := pos_out !outchan;
  125.     fprintf !outchan
  126.             " 0;; Profiling.counters := \
  127.               (\"%s\", (\"%s\", %s%s_cnt)) :: !Profiling.counters;; "
  128.             mod_name modes idprefix mod_name;
  129.   end

  131. let final_rewrite add_function =
  132.   to_insert := List.sort (fun x y -> compare (snd x) (snd y)) !to_insert;
  133.   prof_counter := 0;
  134.   List.iter add_function !to_insert;
  135.   copy (in_channel_length !inchan);
  136.   if !instr_mode then begin
  137.     let len = Int.to_string !prof_counter in
  138.     if String.length len > 9 then raise (Profiler "too many counters");
  139.     seek_out !outchan (!pos_len - String.length len);
  140.     output_string !outchan len
  141.   end
  142.   (* Cannot close because outchan is stdout and Format doesn't like
  143.      a closed stdout.
  144.     close_out !outchan;
  145.   *)

  147. ‌let rec rewrite_patexp_list iflag l =
  148.   rewrite_exp_list iflag (List.map (fun x -> x.pvb_expr) l)

  150. and rewrite_cases iflag l =
  151.   List.iter
  152.     (fun pc ->
  153.       begin match pc.pc_guard with
  154.       | None -> ()
  155.       | Some g -> rewrite_exp iflag g
  156.       end;
  157.       rewrite_exp iflag pc.pc_rhs
  158.     )
  159.     l

  161. and rewrite_labelexp_list iflag l =
  162.   rewrite_exp_list iflag (List.map snd l)

  164. and rewrite_exp_list iflag l =
  165.   List.iter (rewrite_exp iflag) l

  167. and rewrite_exp iflag sexp =
  168.   if iflag then insert_profile rw_exp sexp
  169.            else rw_exp false sexp

  171. and rw_exp iflag sexp =
  172.   match sexp.pexp_desc with
  173.     Pexp_ident _lid -> ()
  174.   | Pexp_constant _cst -> ()

  176.   | Pexp_let(_, spat_sexp_list, sbody) ->
  177.     rewrite_patexp_list iflag spat_sexp_list;
  178.     rewrite_exp iflag sbody

  180.   | Pexp_function caselist ->
  181.     if !instr_fun then
  182.       rewrite_function iflag caselist
  183.     else
  184.       rewrite_cases iflag caselist

  186.   | Pexp_fun (_, _, p, e) ->
  187. ‌      let l = [{pc_lhs=p; pc_guard=None; pc_rhs=e}] in
  188.       if !instr_fun then
  189.         rewrite_function iflag l
  190.       else
  191.         rewrite_cases iflag l

  193.   | Pexp_match(sarg, caselist) ->
  194.     rewrite_exp iflag sarg;
  195.     if !instr_match && not sexp.pexp_loc.loc_ghost then
  196.       rewrite_funmatching caselist
  197.     else
  198.       rewrite_cases iflag caselist

  200.   | Pexp_try(sbody, caselist) ->
  201.     rewrite_exp iflag sbody;
  202.     if !instr_try && not sexp.pexp_loc.loc_ghost then
  203.       rewrite_trymatching caselist
  204.     else
  205.       rewrite_cases iflag caselist

  207.   | Pexp_apply(sfunct, sargs) ->
  208.     rewrite_exp iflag sfunct;
  209.     rewrite_exp_list iflag (List.map snd sargs)

  211.   | Pexp_tuple sexpl ->
  212.     rewrite_exp_list iflag sexpl

  214.   | Pexp_construct(_, None) -> ()
  215.   | Pexp_construct(_, Some sarg) ->
  216.     rewrite_exp iflag sarg

  218.   | Pexp_variant(_, None) -> ()
  219.   | Pexp_variant(_, Some sarg) ->
  220.     rewrite_exp iflag sarg

  222.   | Pexp_record(lid_sexp_list, None) ->
  223.     rewrite_labelexp_list iflag lid_sexp_list
  224.   | Pexp_record(lid_sexp_list, Some sexp) ->
  225.     rewrite_exp iflag sexp;
  226.     rewrite_labelexp_list iflag lid_sexp_list

  228.   | Pexp_field(sarg, _) ->
  229.     rewrite_exp iflag sarg

  231.   | Pexp_setfield(srecord, _, snewval) ->
  232.     rewrite_exp iflag srecord;
  233.     rewrite_exp iflag snewval

  235.   | Pexp_array(sargl) ->
  236.     rewrite_exp_list iflag sargl

  238.   | Pexp_ifthenelse(scond, sifso, None) ->
  239.       rewrite_exp iflag scond;
  240.       rewrite_ifbody iflag sexp.pexp_loc.loc_ghost sifso
  241.   | Pexp_ifthenelse(scond, sifso, Some sifnot) ->
  242.       rewrite_exp iflag scond;
  243.       rewrite_ifbody iflag sexp.pexp_loc.loc_ghost sifso;
  244.       rewrite_ifbody iflag sexp.pexp_loc.loc_ghost sifnot

  246.   | Pexp_sequence(sexp1, sexp2) ->
  247.     rewrite_exp iflag sexp1;
  248.     rewrite_exp iflag sexp2

  250.   | Pexp_while(scond, sbody) ->
  251.     rewrite_exp iflag scond;
  252.     if !instr_loops && not sexp.pexp_loc.loc_ghost
  253.     then insert_profile rw_exp sbody
  254.     else rewrite_exp iflag sbody

  256.   | Pexp_for(_, slow, shigh, _, sbody) ->
  257.     rewrite_exp iflag slow;
  258.     rewrite_exp iflag shigh;
  259.     if !instr_loops && not sexp.pexp_loc.loc_ghost
  260.     then insert_profile rw_exp sbody
  261.     else rewrite_exp iflag sbody

  263.   | Pexp_constraint(sarg, _) | Pexp_coerce(sarg, _, _) ->
  264.     rewrite_exp iflag sarg

  266.   | Pexp_send (sobj, _) ->
  267.     rewrite_exp iflag sobj

  269.   | Pexp_new _ -> ()

  271.   | Pexp_setinstvar (_, sarg) ->
  272.     rewrite_exp iflag sarg

  274.   | Pexp_override l ->
  275.       List.iter (fun (_, sexp) -> rewrite_exp iflag sexp) l

  277.   | Pexp_letmodule (_, smod, sexp) ->
  278.       rewrite_mod iflag smod;
  279.       rewrite_exp iflag sexp

  281.   | Pexp_letexception (_cd, exp) ->
  282.       rewrite_exp iflag exp

  284.   | Pexp_assert (cond) -> rewrite_exp iflag cond

  286.   | Pexp_lazy (expr) -> rewrite_exp iflag expr

  288.   | Pexp_poly (sexp, _) -> rewrite_exp iflag sexp

  290.   | Pexp_object cl ->
  291.       List.iter (rewrite_class_field iflag) cl.pcstr_fields

  293.   | Pexp_newtype (_, sexp) -> rewrite_exp iflag sexp
  294.   | Pexp_open (_, e) -> rewrite_exp iflag e
  295.   | Pexp_pack (smod) -> rewrite_mod iflag smod
  296.   | Pexp_letop {let_; ands; body; _} ->
  297.       rewrite_exp iflag let_.pbop_exp;
  298.       List.iter (fun {pbop_exp; _} -> rewrite_exp iflag pbop_exp) ands;
  299.       rewrite_exp iflag body
  300.   | Pexp_extension _ -> ()
  301.   | Pexp_unreachable -> ()

  303. ‌and rewrite_ifbody iflag ghost sifbody =
  304.   if !instr_if && not ghost then
  305.     insert_profile rw_exp sifbody
  306.   else
  307.     rewrite_exp iflag sifbody

  309. (* called only when !instr_fun *)
  310. and rewrite_annotate_exp_list l =
  311.   List.iter
  312.     (function
  313.      | {pc_guard=Some scond; pc_rhs=sbody} ->
  314.          insert_profile rw_exp scond;
  315.          insert_profile rw_exp sbody;
  316.      | {pc_rhs={pexp_desc = Pexp_constraint(sbody, _)}} (* let f x : t = e *)
  317.         -> insert_profile rw_exp sbody
  318.      | {pc_rhs=sexp} -> insert_profile rw_exp sexp)
  319.     l

  321. and rewrite_function iflag = function
  322.   | [{pc_lhs=_; pc_guard=None;
  323.       pc_rhs={pexp_desc = (Pexp_function _|Pexp_fun _)} as sexp}] ->
  324.         rewrite_exp iflag sexp
  325.   | l -> rewrite_funmatching l

  327. and rewrite_funmatching l =
  328.   rewrite_annotate_exp_list l

  330. and rewrite_trymatching l =
  331.   rewrite_annotate_exp_list l

  333. (* Rewrite a class definition *)

  335. and rewrite_class_field iflag cf =
  336.   match cf.pcf_desc with
  337.     Pcf_inherit (_, cexpr, _)     -> rewrite_class_expr iflag cexpr
  338.   | Pcf_val (_, _, Cfk_concrete (_, sexp))  -> rewrite_exp iflag sexp
  339.   | Pcf_method (_, _,
  340.                 Cfk_concrete (_, ({pexp_desc = (Pexp_function _|Pexp_fun _)}
  341.                                     as sexp))) ->
  342.       rewrite_exp iflag sexp
  343.   | Pcf_method (_, _, Cfk_concrete(_, sexp)) ->
  344.       let loc = cf.pcf_loc in
  345.       if !instr_fun && not loc.loc_ghost then insert_profile rw_exp sexp
  346.       else rewrite_exp iflag sexp
  347.   | Pcf_initializer sexp ->
  348.       rewrite_exp iflag sexp
  349.   | Pcf_method (_, _, Cfk_virtual _)
  350.   | Pcf_val (_, _, Cfk_virtual _)
  351.   | Pcf_constraint _  -> ()
  352.   | Pcf_attribute _ -> ()
  353.   | Pcf_extension _ -> ()

  355. and rewrite_class_expr iflag cexpr =
  356.   match cexpr.pcl_desc with
  357.     Pcl_constr _ -> ()
  358.   | Pcl_structure st ->
  359.       List.iter (rewrite_class_field iflag) st.pcstr_fields
  360.   | Pcl_fun (_, _, _, cexpr) ->
  361.       rewrite_class_expr iflag cexpr
  362.   | Pcl_apply (cexpr, exprs) ->
  363.       rewrite_class_expr iflag cexpr;
  364.       List.iter (rewrite_exp iflag) (List.map snd exprs)
  365.   | Pcl_let (_, spat_sexp_list, cexpr) ->
  366.       rewrite_patexp_list iflag spat_sexp_list;
  367.       rewrite_class_expr iflag cexpr
  368.   | Pcl_open (_, cexpr)
  369.   | Pcl_constraint (cexpr, _) ->
  370.       rewrite_class_expr iflag cexpr
  371.   | Pcl_extension _ -> ()

  373. and rewrite_class_declaration iflag cl =
  374.   rewrite_class_expr iflag cl.pci_expr

  376. (* Rewrite a module expression or structure expression *)

  378. and rewrite_mod iflag smod =
  379.   match smod.pmod_desc with
  380.     Pmod_ident _ -> ()
  381.   | Pmod_structure sstr -> List.iter (rewrite_str_item iflag) sstr
  382.   | Pmod_functor(_param, sbody) -> rewrite_mod iflag sbody
  383.   | Pmod_apply(smod1, smod2) ->
  384.       rewrite_mod iflag smod1;
  385.       rewrite_mod iflag smod2
  386.   | Pmod_apply_unit smod1 ->
  387.       rewrite_mod iflag smod1
  388.   | Pmod_constraint(smod, _smty) -> rewrite_mod iflag smod
  389.   | Pmod_unpack(sexp) -> rewrite_exp iflag sexp
  390.   | Pmod_extension _ -> ()

  392. and rewrite_str_item iflag item =
  393.   match item.pstr_desc with
  394.     Pstr_eval (exp, _attrs) -> rewrite_exp iflag exp
  395.   | Pstr_value(_, exps)
  396.      -> List.iter (fun x -> rewrite_exp iflag x.pvb_expr) exps
  397.   | Pstr_module x -> rewrite_mod iflag x.pmb_expr
  398.         (* todo: Pstr_recmodule?? *)
  399.   | Pstr_class classes -> List.iter (rewrite_class_declaration iflag) classes
  400.   | _ -> ()

  402. (* Rewrite a .ml file *)
  403. ‌let rewrite_file srcfile add_function =
  404.   inchan := open_in_bin srcfile;
  405.   let lb = Lexing.from_channel !inchan in
  406.   Location.input_name := srcfile;
  407.   Location.init lb srcfile;
  408.   List.iter (rewrite_str_item false) (Parse.implementation lb);
  409.   final_rewrite add_function;
  410.   close_in !inchan

  412. (* Copy a non-.ml file without change *)
  413. ‌let null_rewrite srcfile =
  414.   inchan := open_in_bin srcfile;
  415.   copy (in_channel_length !inchan);
  416.   close_in !inchan

  418. (* Setting flags from saved config *)
  419. ‌let set_flags s =
  420.   for i = 0 to String.length s - 1 do
  421.     match String.get s i with
  422.       'f' -> instr_fun := true
  423.     | 'm' -> instr_match := true
  424.     | 'i' -> instr_if := true
  425.     | 'l' -> instr_loops := true
  426.     | 't' -> instr_try := true
  427.     | 'a' -> instr_fun := true; instr_match := true;
  428.              instr_if := true; instr_loops := true;
  429.              instr_try := true
  430.     | _ -> ()
  431.     done

  433. (* Command-line options *)

  435. ‌let modes = ref "fm"
  436. ‌let dumpfile = ref "ocamlprof.dump"

  438. (* Process a file *)

  440. ‌let process_intf_file filename = null_rewrite filename

  442. ‌let process_impl_file filename =
  443.    let modname = Filename.basename(Filename.chop_extension filename) in
  444.        (* FIXME should let modname = String.capitalize modname *)
  445.    if !instr_mode then begin
  446.      (* Instrumentation mode *)
  447.      set_flags !modes;
  448.      init_rewrite !modes modname;
  449.      rewrite_file filename (add_incr_counter modname);
  450.    end else begin
  451.      (* Results mode *)
  452.      let ic = open_in_bin !dumpfile in
  453.      let allcounters =
  454.        (input_value ic : (string * (string * int array)) list) in
  455.      close_in ic;
  456.      let (modes, cv) =
  457.        try
  458.          List.assoc modname allcounters
  459.        with Not_found ->
  460.          raise(Profiler("Module " ^ modname ^ " not used in this profile."))
  461.      in
  462.      counters := cv;
  463.      set_flags modes;
  464.      init_rewrite modes modname;
  465.      rewrite_file filename add_val_counter;
  466.    end

  468. let process_anon_file filename =
  469.   if Filename.check_suffix filename ".ml" then
  470.     process_impl_file filename
  471.   else
  472.     process_intf_file filename

  474. (* Main function *)

  476. open Format

  478. ‌let usage = "Usage: ocamlprof <options> <files>\noptions are:"

  480. ‌let print_version () =
  481.   printf "ocamlprof, version %s@." Sys.ocaml_version;
  482.   exit 0

  484. ‌let print_version_num () =
  485.   printf "%s@." Sys.ocaml_version;
  486.   exit 0

  488. ‌let main () =
  489.   try
  490.     Option.iter Location.(prerr_alert none) @@ Warnings.parse_options false "a";
  491.     Arg.parse_expand [
  492.        "-f", Arg.String (fun s -> dumpfile := s),
  493.              "<file>     Use <file> as dump file (default ocamlprof.dump)";
  494.        "-F", Arg.String (fun s -> special_id := s),
  495.              "<s>        Insert string <s> with the counts";
  496.        "-impl", Arg.String process_impl_file,
  497.                 "<file>  Process <file> as a .ml file";
  498.        "-instrument", Arg.Set instr_mode, "  (undocumented)";
  499.        "-intf", Arg.String process_intf_file,
  500.                 "<file>  Process <file> as a .mli file";
  501.        "-m", Arg.String (fun s -> modes := s), "<flags>    (undocumented)";
  502.        "-version", Arg.Unit print_version,
  503.                    "     Print version and exit";
  504.        "-vnum", Arg.Unit print_version_num,
  505.                 "        Print version number and exit";
  506.         "-args", Arg.Expand Arg.read_arg,
  507.             "<file> Read additional newline separated command line arguments \n\
  508.             \      from <file>";
  509.        "-args0", Arg.Expand Arg.read_arg0,
  510.            "<file> Read additional NUL separated command line arguments from \n\
  511.            \      <file>"
  512.     ] process_anon_file usage;
  513.     exit 0
  514.   with
  515.   | Profiler msg ->
  516.       fprintf Format.err_formatter "@[%s@]@." msg;
  517.       exit 2
  518.   | exn ->
  519.       Location.report_exception Format.err_formatter exn

  521. let _ = main ()
